                            <comment id="12877915" author="techhusky" created="Fri, 11 Jun 2010 19:47:20 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching junit that demonstrates this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12882332" author="techhusky" created="Thu, 24 Jun 2010 22:17:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I added a fix that will correct this issue in most cases.  There is still some quirkiness if/when table or column names contain underscores.  The code makes an attempt at resolving owned sequences in that case, but it could incorrectly identify a sequence as a db owned sequence.  If that happens, the sequence will not get removed during the drop phase.  Still, the best solution is to not create sequences suffixed with _seq, if possible.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
